<p>Over the period from 1800 to 2014, the socio-climate model is simulated with a fixed social component, forced with historical anthropogenic carbon emissions. Initial conditions for all climate variables are zero since they represent deviations from pre-industrial values. Social dynamics are initiated in 2014 with an initial proportion of mitigators 
 <italic>x</italic>
 <sub>0</sub> = 0.05. The ensuing dynamics of 
 <italic>ϵ</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>) follow an increasing but saturating trend corresponding to the world’s increasing but saturating population size and energy demands. Specifically 
